{{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.template.spec.containers.name={{ubuntu}}.imagePullPolicy relies on mutable images in cache \u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExcepted value:\u003c/strong\u003e metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.template.spec.containers.name={{ubuntu}}.imagePullPolicy should be set to 'Always'"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Image Pull Policy of the container must be defined and set to Always Value: metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.template.spec.containers.name={{ubuntu}}.imagePullPolicy relies on mutable images in cache Excepted value: metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.template.spec.containers.name={{ubuntu}}.imagePullPolicy should be set to 'Always'"},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Image Pull Policy Of The Container Is Not Set To Always","id":"Image Pull Policy Of The Container Is Not Set To Always - caa3479d-885d-4882-9aac-95e5e78ef5c2 [Taken from query_id] (kics)","description":"Image Pull Policy of the container must be defined and set to Always Value: metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.template.spec.containers.name={{ubuntu}}.imagePullPolicy relies on mutable images in cache Excepted value: metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.template.spec.containers.name={{ubuntu}}.imagePullPolicy should be set to 'Always'","tags":["security","checkmarx","kics"]}},{"id":"CVE-2025-69873 (sca)","name":"Cve202569873","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"ajv (Another JSON Schema Validator) through version 8.17.1 is vulnerable to Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS) when the \u0026#34;$data\u0026#34; option is enabled. The pattern keyword accepts runtime data via JSON Pointer syntax ($data reference), which is passed directly to the JavaScript \u0026#34;RegExp()\u0026#34; constructor without validation. An attacker can inject a malicious regex pattern (e.g., \u0026#34;^(a|a)*$\u0026#34;) combined with crafted input to cause catastrophic backtracking. A 31-character payload causes approximately 44 seconds of CPU blocking, with each additional character doubling execution time. This enables complete denial of service with a single HTTP request against any API using ajv with $data: true for dynamic schema validation.","markdown":"ajv (Another JSON Schema Validator) through version 8.17.1 is vulnerable to Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS) when the \u0026#34;$data\u0026#34; option is enabled. The pattern keyword accepts runtime data via JSON Pointer syntax ($data reference), which is passed directly to the JavaScript \u0026#34;RegExp()\u0026#34; constructor without validation. An attacker can inject a malicious regex pattern (e.g., \u0026#34;^(a|a)*$\u0026#34;) combined with crafted input to cause catastrophic backtracking. A 31-character payload causes approximately 44 seconds of CPU blocking, with each additional character doubling execution time. This enables complete denial of service with a single HTTP request against any API using ajv with $data: true for dynamic schema validation."},"fullDescription":{"text":"ajv (Another JSON Schema Validator) through version 8.17.1 is vulnerable to Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS) when the \u0026#34;$data\u0026#34; option is enabled. The pattern keyword accepts runtime data via JSON Pointer syntax ($data reference), which is passed directly to the JavaScript \u0026#34;RegExp()\u0026#34; constructor without validation. An attacker can inject a malicious regex pattern (e.g., \u0026#34;^(a|a)*$\u0026#34;) combined with crafted input to cause catastrophic backtracking. A 31-character payload causes approximately 44 seconds of CPU blocking, with each additional character doubling execution time. This enables complete denial of service with a single HTTP request against any API using ajv with $data: true for dynamic schema validation."},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Cve202569873","id":"CVE-2025-69873 (sca)","description":"ajv (Another JSON Schema Validator) through version 8.17.1 is vulnerable to Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS) when the \u0026#34;$data\u0026#34; option is enabled. The pattern keyword accepts runtime data via JSON Pointer syntax ($data reference), which is passed directly to the JavaScript \u0026#34;RegExp()\u0026#34; constructor without validation. An attacker can inject a malicious regex pattern (e.g., \u0026#34;^(a|a)*$\u0026#34;) combined with crafted input to cause catastrophic backtracking. A 31-character payload causes approximately 44 seconds of CPU blocking, with each additional character doubling execution time. This enables complete denial of service with a single HTTP request against any API using ajv with $data: true for dynamic schema validation.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Service Does Not Target Pod - 3ca03a61-3249-4c16-8427-6f8e47dda729 [Taken from query_id] (kics)","name":"Service Does Not Target Pod","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Service should Target a Pod Value: metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.ports.port={{8099}} does not have a Pod port Excepted value: metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.ports.port={{8099}} has a Pod port","markdown":"Service should Target a Pod \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eValue:\u003c/strong\u003e metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.ports.port={{8099}} does not have a Pod port \u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExcepted value:\u003c/strong\u003e metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.ports.port={{8099}} has a Pod port"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Service should Target a Pod Value: metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.ports.port={{8099}} does not have a Pod port Excepted value: metadata.name={{ubuntu-dev}}.spec.ports.port={{8099}} has a Pod port"},"properties":{"security-severity":"2.0","name":"Service Does Not Target Pod","id":"Service Does Not Target Pod - 3ca03a61-3249-4c16-8427-6f8e47dda729 [Taken from query_id] (kics)","description":"Service should Target a Pod Value: metadata.n