 to spoof a crafted response to a UDP request generated by this function and overwrite neighboring static data in the requesting application.\n\nNIS support is obsolete and has been deprecated in the GNU C Library since version 2.26 and is only maintained for legacy usage. Applications should port away from NIS to more modern identity and access management services."},"fullDescription":{"text":"The obsolete nis_local_principal function in the GNU C Library versions prior to  2.43 may overflow a buffer in the data section, which could allow an attacker to spoof a crafted response to a UDP request generated by this function and overwrite neighboring static data in the requesting application.\n\nNIS support is obsolete and has been deprecated in the GNU C Library since version 2.26 and is only maintained for legacy usage. Applications should port away from NIS to more modern identity and access management services."},"properties":{"security-severity":"1.0","name":"Cve20265358","id":"CVE-2026-5358 (containers)","description":"The obsolete nis_local_principal function in the GNU C Library versions prior to  2.43 may overflow a buffer in the data section, which could allow an attacker to spoof a crafted response to a UDP request generated by this function and overwrite neighboring static data in the requesting application.\n\nNIS support is obsolete and has been deprecated in the GNU C Library since version 2.26 and is only maintained for legacy usage. Applications should port away from NIS to more modern identity and access management services.","tags":["security","checkmarx","containers"]}},{"id":"CVE-2026-0915 (containers)","name":"Cve20260915","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Calling \u0026#34;getnetbyaddr\u0026#34; or \u0026#34;getnetbyaddr_r\u0026#34; with a configured \u0026#34;nsswitch.conf\u0026#34; that specifies the library\u0026#39;s DNS backend for networks and queries for a zero-valued network in the GNU C Library versions 2.0 through 2.42 can leak stack contents to the configured DNS resolver.","markdown":"Calling \u0026#34;getnetbyaddr\u0026#34; or \u0026#34;getnetbyaddr_r\u0026#34; with a configured \u0026#34;nsswitch.conf\u0026#34; that specifies the library\u0026#39;s DNS backend for networks and queries for a zero-valued network in the GNU C Library versions 2.0 through 2.42 can leak stack contents to the configured DNS resolver."},"fullDescription":{"text":"Calling \u0026#34;getnetbyaddr\u0026#34; or \u0026#34;getnetbyaddr_r\u0026#34; with a configured \u0026#34;nsswitch.conf\u0026#34; that specifies the library\u0026#39;s DNS backend for networks and queries for a zero-valued network in the GNU C Library versions 2.0 through 2.42 can leak stack contents to the configured DNS resolver."},"properties":{"security-severity":"1.0","name":"Cve20260915","id":"CVE-2026-0915 (containers)","description":"Calling \u0026#34;getnetbyaddr\u0026#34; or \u0026#34;getnetbyaddr_r\u0026#34; with a configured \u0026#34;nsswitch.conf\u0026#34; that specifies the library\u0026#39;s DNS backend for networks and queries for a zero-valued network in the GNU C Library versions 2.0 through 2.42 can leak stack contents to the configured DNS resolver.","tags":["security","checkmarx","containers"]}},{"id":"Missing Default Case In Switch Statement - 1415321839264458646 (sast)","name":"Missing Default Case In Switch Statement","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"","markdown":""},"fullDescription":{"text":""},"properties":{"security-severity":"1.0","name":"Missing Default Case In Switch Statement","id":"Missing Default Case In Switch Statement - 1415321839264458646 (sast)","description":"","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"APT-GET Not Avoiding Additional Packages - 7384dfb2-fcd1-4fbf-91cd-6c44c318c33c [Taken from query_id] (kics)","name":"APT-GET Not Avoiding Additional Packages","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"Check if any apt-get installs don\u0026#39;t use \u0026#39;--no-install-recommends\u0026#39; flag to avoid installing additional packages. Value: 'RUN curl -fsSL https://cli.github.com/packages/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg | dd of=/usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg \t\u0026\u0026 chmod go+r /usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg \t\u0026\u0026 echo \"deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg] https://cli.github.com/packages stable main\" | tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/github-cli.list \u003e /dev/null \t\u0026\u0026 apt-get update \u0026\u0026 apt-get -y install     gh   \u0026\u0026 rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*   \u0026\u0026 apt-get clean   \u0026\u0026 apt-get autoremove -y' does not use '--no-install-recommends' flag to avoid installing additional packages Excepted value: 'RUN curl -fsSL https://cli.github.com/packages/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg | dd of=/usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg \t\u0026\u0026 chmod go+r /usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg \t\u0026\u0026 echo \"deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg] https://cli.github.com/packages stable main\" | tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/github-cli.list \u003e /dev/null \t\u0026\u0026 apt-get update \u0026\u0026 apt-get -y install     gh   \u0026\u0026 rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*   \u0026\u0026 apt-get clean   \u0026\u0026 apt-get autoremove -y' uses '--no-install-recommends' flag to avoid installing additional packages","markdown":"Check if any apt-get installs don\u0026#39;t use \u0026#39;--no-install-recommends\u0026#39; flag to avoid installing additional packages. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eValue:\u003c/strong\u003e 'RUN curl -fsSL https://cli.github.com/packages/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg | dd of=/usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg \t\u0026\u0026 chmod go+r /usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg \t\u0026\u0026 echo \"deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg] https://cli.github.com/packages stable main\" | tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/github-cli.list \u003e /dev/null \t\u0026\u0026 apt-get update \u0026\u0026 apt-get -y install     gh   \u0026\u0026 rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*   \u0026\u0026 apt-get clean   \u0026\u0026 apt-get autoremove -y' does not use '--no-install-recommends' flag to avoid installing additional packages \u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExcepted value:\u003c/strong\u003e 'RUN curl -fsSL https://cli.github.com/packages/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg | dd of=/usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg \t\u0026\u0026 chmod go+r /usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg \t\u0026\u0026 echo \"deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg] https://cli.github.com/packages stable main\" | tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/github-cli.list \u003e /dev/null \t\u0026\u0026 apt-get update \u0026\u0026 apt-get -y install     gh   \u0026\u0026 rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*   \u0026\u0026 apt-get clean   \u0026\u0026 apt-get autoremove -y' uses '--no-install-recommends' flag to avoid installing additional packages"},"fullDescription":{"text":"Check if any apt-get installs don\u0026#39;t use \u0026#39;--no-install-recommends\u0026#39; flag to avoid installing additional packages. Value: 'RUN curl -fsSL https://cli.github.com/packages/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg | dd of=/usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg \t\u0026\u0026 chmod go+r /usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg \t\u0026\u0026 echo \"deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg] https://cli.github.com/packages stable main\" | tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/github-cli.list \u003e /dev/null \t\u0026\u0026 apt-get update \u0