dditional packages Excepted value: 'RUN curl -fsSL https://cli.github.com/packages/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg | dd of=/usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg \t\u0026\u0026 chmod go+r /usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg \t\u0026\u0026 echo \"deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/githubcli-archive-keyring.gpg] https://cli.github.com/packages stable main\" | tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/github-cli.list \u003e /dev/null \t\u0026\u0026 apt-get update \u0026\u0026 apt-get -y install     gh   \u0026\u0026 rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*   \u0026\u0026 apt-get clean   \u0026\u0026 apt-get autoremove -y' uses '--no-install-recommends' flag to avoid installing additional packages","tags":["security","checkmarx","kics"]}},{"id":"Apt Get Install Lists Were Not Deleted - df746b39-6564-4fed-bf85-e9c44382303c [Taken from query_id] (kics)","name":"Apt Get Install Lists Were Not Deleted","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"After using apt-get install, it is needed to delete apt-get lists Value: After using apt-get install, the apt-get lists were not deleted Excepted value: After using apt-get install, the apt-get lists should be deleted","markdown":"After using apt-get install, it is needed to delete apt-get lists \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eValue:\u003c/strong\u003e After using apt-get install, the apt-get lists were not deleted \u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExcepted value:\u003c/strong\u003e After using apt-get install, the apt-get lists should be deleted"},"fullDescription":{"text":"After using apt-get install, it is needed to delete apt-get lists Value: After using apt-get install, the apt-get lists were not deleted Excepted value: After using apt-get install, the apt-get lists should be deleted"},"properties":{"security-severity":"1.0","name":"Apt Get Install Lists Were Not Deleted","id":"Apt Get Install Lists Were Not Deleted - df746b39-6564-4fed-bf85-e9c44382303c [Taken from query_id] (kics)","description":"After using apt-get install, it is needed to delete apt-get lists Value: After using apt-get install, the apt-get lists were not deleted Excepted value: After using apt-get install, the apt-get lists should be deleted","tags":["security","checkmarx","kics"]}},{"id":"Cxa83491f0-29a9 (sca)","name":"Cxa83491f029a9","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The esbuild Deno module (`lib/deno/mod.ts`) downloads native binary executables from an npm registry and writes them to disk with executable permissions (`0o755`) **without performing any integrity verification** (e.g., SHA-256 hash check). The Node.js equivalent (`lib/npm/node-install.ts`) includes a robust `binaryIntegrityCheck()` function that verifies SHA-256 hashes against hardcoded expected values from `package.json`, but this protection was never implemented for the Deno distribution. The affected versions are prior to 0.28.1.","markdown":"The esbuild Deno module (`lib/deno/mod.ts`) downloads native binary executables from an npm registry and writes them to disk with executable permissions (`0o755`) **without performing any integrity verification** (e.g., SHA-256 hash check). The Node.js equivalent (`lib/npm/node-install.ts`) includes a robust `binaryIntegrityCheck()` function that verifies SHA-256 hashes against hardcoded expected values from `package.json`, but this protection was never implemented for the Deno distribution. The affected versions are prior to 0.28.1."},"fullDescription":{"text":"The esbuild Deno module (`lib/deno/mod.ts`) downloads native binary executables from an npm registry and writes them to disk with executable permissions (`0o755`) **without performing any integrity verification** (e.g., SHA-256 hash check). The Node.js equivalent (`lib/npm/node-install.ts`) includes a robust `binaryIntegrityCheck()` function that verifies SHA-256 hashes against hardcoded expected values from `package.json`, but this protection was never implemented for the Deno distribution. The affected versions are prior to 0.28.1."},"properties":{"security-severity":"1.0","name":"Cxa83491f029a9","id":"Cxa83491f0-29a9 (sca)","description":"The esbuild Deno module (`lib/deno/mod.ts`) downloads native binary executables from an npm registry and writes them to disk with executable permissions (`0o755`) **without performing any integrity verification** (e.g., SHA-256 hash check). The Node.js equivalent (`lib/npm/node-install.ts`) includes a robust `binaryIntegrityCheck()` function that verifies SHA-256 hashes against hardcoded expected values from `package.json`, but this protection was never implemented for the Deno distribution. The affected versions are prior to 0.28.1.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sca"]}},{"id":"Hardcoded Absolute Path - 4287919870914542957 (sast)","name":"Hardcoded Absolute Path","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"The Lambda method references external files using a hard-coded, absolute path \u0026#34;C:\\\\path\\\\to\\\\dir\\\\\u0026#34; in /frontend/__tests__/components/features/chat/path-component.test.tsx at line 15.","markdown":"The Lambda method references external files using a hard-coded, absolute path \u0026#34;C:\\\\path\\\\to\\\\dir\\\\\u0026#34; in /frontend/__tests__/components/features/chat/path-component.test.tsx at line 15."},"fullDescription":{"text":"The Lambda method references external files using a hard-coded, absolute path \u0026#34;C:\\\\path\\\\to\\\\dir\\\\\u0026#34; in /frontend/__tests__/components/features/chat/path-component.test.tsx at line 15."},"properties":{"security-severity":"1.0","name":"Hardcoded Absolute Path","id":"Hardcoded Absolute Path - 4287919870914542957 (sast)","description":"The Lambda method references external files using a hard-coded, absolute path \u0026#34;C:\\\\path\\\\to\\\\dir\\\\\u0026#34; in /frontend/__tests__/components/features/chat/path-component.test.tsx at line 15.","tags":["security","checkmarx","sast"]}},{"id":"Ensure Administrative Boundaries Between Resources - e84eaf4d-2f45-47b2-abe8-e581b06deb66 [Taken from query_id] (kics)","name":"Ensure Administrative Boundaries Between Resources","helpUri":"https://checkmarx.com/resource/documents/en/34965-67042-checkmarx-one.html","help":{"text":"As a best practice, ensure that is made the correct use of namespaces to adequately administer your resources. Kubernetes Authorization plugins can also be used to create policies that segregate user access to namespaces. Value: namespaces in use: default, ingress-nginx Excepted value: ensure that these namespaces are the ones you need and are adequately administered as per your requirements.","markdown":"As a best practice, ensure that is made the correct use of namespaces to adequately administer your resources. Kubernetes Authorization plugins can also be used to create policies that segregate user access to namespaces. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eValue:\u003c/strong\u003e namespaces in use: default, ingress-nginx \u003cbr\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eExcepted value:\u003c/strong\u003e ensure that these namespaces are the ones you need and are adequately administered as per your requirements."},"fullDescription":{"text":"As a best practice, ensure that is made the correct use of namespaces to adequately administer your resources. Kubernetes Authorization plugins can also be used to create policies that segregate user access to namespaces. Value: namespaces in use: default, ingress-nginx Excepted value: ensure that these namespaces are the ones you need and are adequately administered as per your requirements."},"properties":{"security-severity":"1.0","name":"Ensure Administrative Boundaries Between Resources","id":"Ensure Administrative Boundaries Between Resources - e84eaf4d-2f45-47b2-abe8-e581b06deb66 [Taken from query_id] (kics)","description":"As a bes